    # ── SAMPLE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Sample_VouchEmailsSalesMotion_20260610
      a narr:Sample ;
      dct:title "The Vouch emails as the original sales motion" ;
      dct:created "2026-06-10"^^xsd:date ;
      dct:description "Part 1 of consulting-engagement session record (June 10-12, 2026). Scarlet Dame and Claude working session. Examines the two emails that won Scarlet the Vouch chief strategist role as a template for a sales motion: person-first outreach through named human threads, a values-resonance call, a 48-hour unsolicited bespoke artifact (the deli story), and conversion to a durable container. The 2026 translation maps this to aswritten's current sales motion." ;
      narr:inputLength 2041 .

    narr:Actor_TonyMaley_VouchRef
      a narr:Actor ;
      skos:prefLabel "Tony Maley (Vouch)" ;
      skos:note "Tony Maley at Vouch; Scarlet's first call with Tony was the trigger for the deli story email sent hours later. The deli story performed narrative strategy on Vouch itself, unsolicited and free, and effectively hired Scarlet on the spot." .

    # ── NARRATIVES ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_VouchEmailSalesMotionTemplate

      dct:source narr:Sample_VouchEmailsSalesMotion_20260610 ;
      skos:broader narr:SalesDecks ;
      skos:prefLabel "The Vouch Email Four-Step Sales Motion Template" ;
      skos:note "The two Vouch emails are a template for a motion, not for words. Step 1: person-first outreach through named human threads, with an honest account of situation and a small ask. Step 2: a call that runs on values resonance, listening for the other person's live tension. Step 3: within 48 hours, an unsolicited bespoke artifact that does the work on them — generosity as demonstration. Step 4: the relationship converts into a durable container. This is the founding instance of the sales-as-delivery pattern, predating aswritten." ;
      narr:theme "A four-step sales motion — person-first outreach, values-resonance call, 48-hour unsolicited bespoke artifact, durable container — is the template underlying Scarlet's most effective sales communication" ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_SalesAsDelivery .

    narr:Narrative_GenerosityAsDemonstration

      dct:source narr:Sample_VouchEmailsSalesMotion_20260610 ;
      skos:broader narr:SalesDecks ;
      skos:prefLabel "Generosity as Demonstration: The 48-Hour Bespoke Artifact" ;
      skos:note "The deli story email was sent hours after the first call with Tony Maley — unsolicited and free. It performed narrative strategy on Vouch itself, rebranding the company and effectively hiring Scarlet on the spot. The pattern: within 48 hours of a values-resonance call, deliver an unsolicited bespoke artifact that does the work on the prospect. Generosity is the demonstration. In the 2026 translation, this becomes systematic: with permission, the prospect's own first call is extracted into a demo perspective branch — the deli story manufactured from the conversation itself." ;
      narr:theme "The most effective sales move is an unsolicited bespoke artifact delivered within 48 hours of a values-resonance call — generosity as demonstration, not pitch" ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_PerspectiveOnSpec .

    narr:Narrative_DeliStoryReframe

      dct:source narr:Sample_VouchEmailsSalesMotion_20260610 ;
      skos:broader narr:NarrativeAnchor ;
      skos:prefLabel "The Deli Story Reframe: The Only Time She Sold 'My Thing, Done for You'" ;
      skos:note "The session's reframe: the deli email is the only time Scarlet has ever sold 'my thing, done for you' — and it is the most effective piece of sales communication she has ever written. She just didn't invoice it. The deli story's core: describing her regular sandwich shop where a new employee replaced the one who knew her order. The insight: 'I don't want to prove my credentials, I just want to be recognized and treated as the regular I am.' This reframes the Vouch pitch from credentials to recognition, from power to invitation. The 2026 translation: the honest line becomes founder transparency ('I'm building aswritten; I take a small number of engagements to fund the build'), which also explains why someone this senior is available part-time." ;
      narr:theme "The deli story is the founding instance of 'my thing, done for you' — the most effective sales communication Scarlet has ever written, delivered as a gift, not an invoice" ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_SalesAsDelivery .

    # ── CLAIMS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
